Wash and dry produce (except green beans).

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and finely chop @scallions{4}. Halve @lime{1}; cut one half into wedges.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add 1 TBSP ginger. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook, covered, until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Cauliflower Rice ==

Cook ginger as instructed. Add @riced cauliflower{12%oz} (no need to drain), a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and any excess liquid has absorbed, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> Save jasmine rice for another use.

== Scallion Gochujang Pesto ==

While rice cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine scallions, @sesame oil{1%tbsp}, half the @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, 1 tsp ginger, @sugar{1%tsp}, juice from half the lime, and @gochujang sauce{1/2%oz} to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; add more ginger or lime juice to taste.

> For more servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil, 2 tsp ginger, and 2 tsp sugar.

== Tilapia ==

Pat @tilapia{11%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add tilapia and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat.

== Green Beans ==

While tilapia cooks, pierce @green beans{6%oz} bag with a fork; place bag on a #plate{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> No microwave? No problem! Steam green beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Transfer green beans to a second medium bowl; add @butter{1%tbsp}. Stir until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and green beans between plates. Arrange tilapia over rice; drizzle with scallion gochujang pesto and @soy sauce{2%tbsp} to taste. Serve with lime wedges on the side.